Document: DirectionalLight3D
Path: godot/classes/class_directionallight3d.rst
Summary: Represents a directional light source, simulating a distant light like the sun.

DirectionalLight3D

Inherits: Light3D < GeometryInstance3D < Node3D < Node

A directional light simulates a distant light source, such as the sun. It emits light in a specific direction, and all rays are parallel. This makes it suitable for simulating outdoor lighting conditions.

Properties:
	shadow_bias (float): The bias value for shadow mapping. This helps to avoid self-shadowing artifacts. Default: 0.0.
	shadow_normal_bias (float): The normal bias value for shadow mapping. This helps to avoid self-shadowing artifacts when surfaces are nearly parallel to the light rays. Default: 0.0.
	shadow_reverse_cull_face (bool): If true, the shadow rendering will reverse the culling face. This can be useful in certain scenarios to ensure correct shadow rendering. Default: false.
	shadow_split_horizontal_offset (float): The horizontal offset for shadow splits. This affects how the shadow map is divided for cascaded shadow maps. Default: 0.0.
	shadow_split_vertical_offset (float): The vertical offset for shadow splits. This affects how the shadow map is divided for cascaded shadow maps. Default: 0.0.
	orographic_shadow_offset (float): The offset for orographic shadows. This is used to adjust the position of shadows cast by terrain or other elevated surfaces. Default: 0.0.
	sky_only (bool): If true, the light will only affect the sky. This is useful for simulating ambient lighting without affecting scene objects. Default: false.
	distance_fade_start (float): The distance at which the light starts to fade out. Default: 0.0.
	distance_fade_length (float): The length of the fade-out distance. Default: 0.0.
	distance_fade_mode (int): The mode for distance fading. Default: 0.

Methods:
	_get_visibility_range(): Returns the visibility range of the light.
	_set_visibility_range(range: float): Sets the visibility range of the light.
