Document: DirectionalLight3D
Path: godot/classes/class_directionallight3d.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the DirectionalLight3D node, which simulates a distant light source like the sun.

Properties
* directional_shadow_blend_splits (bool): Controls whether shadow splits blend smoothly. Default: false.
* directional_shadow_fade_start (float): The distance from the camera where shadows start to fade out. Default: 0.8.
* directional_shadow_max_distance (float): The maximum distance at which shadows are rendered. Default: 100.0.
* directional_shadow_mode (ShadowMode): The mode used for rendering directional shadows. Default: 2.
* directional_shadow_pancake_size (float): Adjusts the size of the shadow "pancakes" for directional lights. Default: 20.0.
* directional_shadow_split_1 (float): The distance for the first shadow split. Default: 0.1.
* directional_shadow_split_2 (float): The distance for the second shadow split. Default: 0.2.
* directional_shadow_split_3 (float): The distance for the third shadow split. Default: 0.5.
* sky_mode (SkyMode): Determines how the directional light interacts with the sky. Default: 0.
---CHUNK---
Document: DirectionalLight3D
Path: godot/classes/class_directionallight3d.rst
Summary: Defines shadow rendering modes and sky interaction modes for DirectionalLight3D.

Enumerations
enum ShadowMode:
  SHADOW_ORTHOGONAL = 0
    Renders the entire scene's shadow map from an orthogonal point of view. This is the fastest directional shadow mode. May result in blurrier shadows on close objects.
  SHADOW_PARALLEL_2_SPLITS = 1
    Splits the view frustum in 2 areas, each with its own shadow map. This shadow mode is a compromise between SHADOW_ORTHOGONAL and SHADOW_PARALLEL_4_SPLITS in terms of performance.
  SHADOW_PARALLEL_4_SPLITS = 2
    Splits the view frustum in 4 areas, each with its own shadow map. This is the slowest directional shadow mode.

enum SkyMode:
  SKY_MODE_LIGHT_AND_SKY = 0
    Makes the light visible in both scene lighting and sky rendering.
  SKY_MODE_LIGHT_ONLY = 1
    Makes the light visible in scene lighting only (including direct lighting and global illumination). When using this mode, the light will not be visible from sky shaders.
  SKY_MODE_SKY_ONLY = 2
    Makes the light visible to sky shaders only. When using this mode the light will not cast light into the scene (either through direct lighting or through global illumination), but can be accessed through sky shaders. This can be useful, for example, when you want to control sky effects without illuminating the scene (during a night cycle, for example).
---CHUNK---
Document: DirectionalLight3D
Path: godot/classes/class_directionallight3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties related to shadow rendering and sky visibility for the DirectionalLight3D node.

Property: directional_shadow_blend_splits
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, shadow detail is sacrificed for smoother transitions between shadow splits. Enabling this has a moderate performance cost and is ignored when directional_shadow_mode is SHADOW_ORTHOGONAL.
Method: set_blend_splits(value: bool)
Method: is_blend_splits_enabled()

Property: directional_shadow_fade_start
Type: float
Default: 0.8
Description: Proportion of directional_shadow_max_distance at which shadows begin to fade. At directional_shadow_max_distance, shadows will disappear. Lowering this value can make shadow transitions less noticeable if the camera moves fast or directional_shadow_max_distance is low. Setting it to 1.0 prevents fading, causing shadows to cut off suddenly.
Method: set_param(value: float)
Method: get_param()

Property: directional_shadow_max_distance
Type: float
Default: 100.0
Description: The maximum distance for shadow splits. Increasing this value makes shadows visible from further away but reduces overall shadow detail and performance.
Method: set_param(value: float)
Method: get_param()

Property: directional_shadow_mode
Type: ShadowMode
Default: 2
Description: The light's shadow rendering algorithm.
Method: set_shadow_mode(value: ShadowMode)
Method: get_shadow_mode()

Property: directional_shadow_pancake_size
Type: float
Default: 20.0
Description: Sets the size of the directional shadow pancake, which offsets the shadow camera frustum for higher depth resolution. A high pancake size can cause artifacts on large objects near the frustum edge. Reducing the size can help. Setting to 0 disables the effect.
Method: set_param(value: float)
Method: get_param()

Property: directional_shadow_split_1
Type: float
Default: 0.1
Description: The distance from the camera to shadow split 1, relative to directional_shadow_max_distance. Used only when directional_shadow_mode is SHADOW_PARALLEL_2_SPLITS or SHADOW_PARALLEL_4_SPLITS.
Method: set_param(value: float)
Method: get_param()

Property: directional_shadow_split_2
Type: float
Default: 0.2
Description: The distance from shadow split 1 to split 2, relative to directional_shadow_max_distance. Used only when directional_shadow_mode is SHADOW_PARALLEL_4_SPLITS.
Method: set_param(value: float)
Method: get_param()

Property: directional_shadow_split_3
Type: float
Default: 0.5
Description: The distance from shadow split 2 to split 3, relative to directional_shadow_max_distance. Used only when directional_shadow_mode is SHADOW_PARALLEL_4_SPLITS.
Method: set_param(value: float)
Method: get_param()

Property: sky_mode
Type: SkyMode
Default: 0
Description: Determines whether this DirectionalLight3D is visible in the sky, in the scene, or both.
Method: set_sky_mode(value: SkyMode)
Method: get_sky_mode()